The political leadership in Egypt supports cooperation in the field of transport with the African and Nile-basin countries, Transport Minister Hesham Arafat said. Egyptian President Abdel Fattah El Sisi launched, a major initiative on a railway line binding Cairo and South Africa's Cape Town, the minister told MENA correspondent in Khartoum on the sidelines of a meeting in Khartoum. In the meantime, Arafat especially described horizons for transport cooperation with Sudan as promising.